<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - ELECTRONIC
        ENGINE CONTROLS - CATERPILLAR - 1992 - 1993 - TROUBLESHOOTING - CLUTCH SWITCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x0813804" svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CLUTCH SWITCH</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the vehicle is equipped with an Allison WT transmission, this switch is replaced with a
                        jumper connection.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Before beginning this test procedure, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins, wires
                        etc. (Refer to paragraph
                        <hotlnk document="s08138_18.xml" xrefid="x0813814">Visual Inspection</hotlnk>
                        in Inspecting Connectors.)
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to paragraph
                <hotlnk xrefid="x0813804">Clutch Switch</hotlnk>
                for description of circuit operation.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Clutch Switch And Circuits</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0813817">Figure 17</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0813818">Figure 18</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0813817" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0813817" filename="../figg08/G0813817.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Testing Clutch Switch And Circuits</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0813818" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0813818" filename="../figg08/G0813818.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Testing Clutch Switch And Circuits (Cont.)</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Adjusting Clutch Switch</title>
            <para>The clutch switch should be mounted so that the switch actuator makes contact with the clutch pedal
                arm when the arm is depressed 0.5 inch at the point of actuator contact. The bracket can be bent forward
                or backward for adjustment. An audible click (switch closing) should be heard when the pedal is
                released.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
